/**
 * @file api_groups.dox
 * @brief High-level API grouping and namespace overview for generated docs.
 */

/**
 * @namespace nn
 * @brief Root namespace for all public NeuralNetCpp APIs.
 */

/**
 * @page guides Guides
 * @brief Practical usage walkthroughs for every major API area.
 *
 * These pages complement the API reference with annotated code examples,
 * recommended patterns, and common pitfalls for each subsystem.
 *
 * @subpage tensor_guide
 *
 * @subpage module_guide
 *
 * @subpage loss_guide
 *
 * @subpage optimizer_guide
 */

/**
 * @defgroup tensor_api Tensor API
 * @brief Dense tensor primitives, shape transforms, math operations, and autograd.
 *
 * Start here when working on numeric data representation and transformation.
 * This group covers storage, indexing, element-wise and matrix operations,
 * reductions, shape utilities, and gradient-related helpers.
 *
 * See the @ref tensor_guide for a usage walkthrough.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup module_api Module API
 * @brief Layer abstractions and trainable module interfaces.
 *
 * Use this group when defining or extending trainable components. It includes
 * the base Module contract and built-in trainable/stateless layer wrappers.
 *
 * See the @ref module_guide for a usage walkthrough.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup sequential_api Sequential API
 * @brief Layer container utilities for ordered model composition.
 *
 * This group documents the high-level container used to compose layers into a
 * feed-forward pipeline with unified parameter collection and mode control.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup activation_api Activation API
 * @brief Stateless nonlinear activation helper functions.
 *
 * Prefer these helpers for pure tensor transformations and custom module
 * implementations where a standalone nonlinearity is required.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup loss_api Loss API
 * @brief Supervised-learning loss functions.
 *
 * This group contains objective functions used during optimization. Each
 * function validates shape assumptions and returns a scalar tensor loss.
 *
 * See the @ref loss_guide for a usage walkthrough.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup optimizer_api Optimizer API
 * @brief Parameter update rules used for training.
 *
 * Optimizers consume parameter tensors and apply in-place updates from
 * accumulated gradients. Choose SGD for simplicity or Adam for adaptive steps.
 *
 * See the @ref optimizer_guide for a usage walkthrough.
 */
